            <h2>What is a PDF Watermark?</h2>
            <p>A PDF watermark is a recognizable image, text, or pattern that appears on one or more pages of a PDF document. Watermarks are typically semi-transparent and positioned behind or over the document content. Common uses include marking documents as "CONFIDENTIAL," "DRAFT," "SAMPLE," or "COPYRIGHT," adding company logos for branding, or protecting intellectual property from unauthorized use. Our PDF watermarker allows you to add professional watermarks to your documents with complete control over appearance, position, and opacity.</p>
            
