            <p>Adding watermarks to PDF documents offers numerous advantages for businesses, legal professionals, content creators, and individuals:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Protect Intellectual Property:</strong> Discourage unauthorized copying and distribution of your content.</li>
                <li><strong>Mark Document Status:</strong> Indicate draft, confidential, approved, or sample status clearly.</li>
                <li><strong>Brand Your Documents:</strong> Add company logos or brand names to all pages for professional presentation.</li>
                <li><strong>Copyright Protection:</strong> Assert ownership and copyright of your creative work.</li>
                <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> Add required disclaimers or notices to documents.</li>
                <li><strong>Prevent Unauthorized Use:</strong> Make it difficult for others to claim your work as their own.</li>
                <li><strong>Internal Document Control:</strong> Mark documents with department names or clearance levels.</li>
                <li><strong>Client Proofing:</strong> Add "SAMPLE" or "PROOF" watermarks to client review copies.</li>
            </ul>
            
