            <h2>Understanding Watermark Options</h2>
            
            <h3>Text Watermarks</h3>
            <p>Text watermarks are ideal for status indicators (CONFIDENTIAL, DRAFT, SAMPLE), copyright notices, or simple branding. They're easy to customize and don't require external image files. Common text watermarks include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>CONFIDENTIAL</strong> - For sensitive internal documents</li>
                <li><strong>DRAFT</strong> - For documents still in review</li>
                <li><strong>SAMPLE</strong> - For client proofs or demo versions</li>
                <li><strong>COPYRIGHT</strong> - For intellectual property protection</li>
                <li><strong>DO NOT COPY</strong> - To discourage unauthorized distribution</li>
                <li><strong>Company Name</strong> - For branding and ownership assertion</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Image Watermarks</h3>
            <p>Image watermarks are perfect for company logos, signatures, seals, or custom graphics. Upload PNG or JPG files (PNG recommended for transparency support). Image watermarks appear as semi-transparent overlays on your document pages.</p>
            
            <h3>Opacity (Transparency)</h3>
            <p>Opacity controls how transparent your watermark appears. Lower opacity (10-30%) creates subtle watermarks that don't interfere with document readability. Higher opacity (50-70%) creates more visible watermarks for stronger protection. We recommend 30% for most use cases.</p>
            
            <h3>Rotation</h3>
            <p>Rotation angles your watermark diagonally across the page. Diagonal watermarks (30-60 degrees) are traditional and cover more page area without obscuring content. Straight watermarks (0 degrees) appear horizontal; vertical (90 degrees) appears top-to-bottom.</p>
            
            <h3>Position</h3>
            <p>Choose where your watermark appears on each page:</p>
            <ul>
